Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, has urged Nigerians to stop blaming President Muhammadu Buhari for all the challenges witnessed in the country. Amaechi, who is a former Chairman of the Nigerian Governors’ Forum, stated this on a Channels Television’s programme titled, ‘Hard Copy.’ The minister argued that Buhari was being blamed for even things that didn’t concern him. Also Read: Insecurity Will Soon Be History, Says Buhari In Christmas Message “The point is we all blame the government. Like the President would say, if tomorrow you are unable to get pregnant, you will blame Buhari,” he said. When asked if the All Progressives Congress did not know about the challenges when it promised to deliver “change” to Nigeria, Amaechi said they didn’t know the magnitude of the rot.